<i>ROCKO'S MODERN LIFE.</i>

00:24.774 --> 00:27.569
(<i> whistling and buzzing</i> )

00:28.236 --> 00:28.278
(<i> splat!</i> )

00:28.862 --> 00:30.947
(<i> screaming</i> )

00:31.030 --> 00:33.950
♪ ROCKO'S MODERN LIFE. ♪

00:34.033 --> 00:35.201
<i>ROCKO'S MODERN LIFE.</i>

00:37.287 --> 00:42.375
[Captioning sponsored by THE
U.S. DEPARTMENT OF EDUCATION]

00:42.459 --> 00:45.003
THAT WAS A HOOT!

00:57.348 --> 01:00.894
(<i> car horn beeping repeatedly</i> )

01:00.977 --> 01:02.187
COME ON...

01:02.270 --> 01:03.646
COME ON, HEFF.

01:03.730 --> 01:05.815
I TOLD YOU TO BE READY AT 8:00.

01:05.899 --> 01:06.816
(<i> loud creaking</i> )

01:06.900 --> 01:10.487
(<i> imitates skiing noises</i> )

01:10.570 --> 01:11.362
HEY, ROCKO.

01:11.446 --> 01:12.947
HEFF, WHAT ARE YOU DOING?

01:13.031 --> 01:15.742
{\an1}SINCE WE'RE GOING
THROUGH THE MOUNTAINS

01:15.825 --> 01:16.993
COULD WE GO SKIING?

01:17.076 --> 01:20.371
(<i> continues making noises</i> )

01:20.455 --> 01:23.166
HEFF, COME ON, GET DOWN,
WE GOT TO GO.

01:23.249 --> 01:24.250
WHY?

01:24.334 --> 01:25.502
(<i> continues making noises</i> )

01:25.585 --> 01:28.296
{\an1}I PROMISED MY BOSS
WE WOULDN'T GOOF OFF.

01:31.007 --> 01:34.844
ROCKO, I WANT YOU TO PICK UP
A SHIPMENT OF BIGMAN COMICS

01:34.928 --> 01:36.971
ON THE OTHER SIDE
OF THE MOUNTAINS.

01:37.055 --> 01:40.183
{\an1}HERE'S MONEY TO BUY THEM,
AND EXTRA FOR GAS AND FOOD.

01:40.266 --> 01:43.186
{\an1}<i>REMEMBER--</i> BUY THE COMICS
AND COME DIRECTLY HOME.

01:43.269 --> 01:45.188
(<i> shouting</i> ):
AND NO GOOFING OFF!

01:48.566 --> 01:49.859
SO SIT TIGHT

01:49.943 --> 01:51.861
AND ENJOY
THE RIDE, OKAY?

01:51.945 --> 01:53.530
(<i> tires screech</i> )

01:56.241 --> 01:57.575
(<i> engine backfiring</i> )

01:57.659 --> 02:00.620
{\an4}Heffer:
♪ HOT CROSS BUNS,
HOT CROSS BUNS ♪

02:00.703 --> 02:03.623
♪ HOT CROSS BUNS,
MMM, MMM, GOOD ♪

02:03.706 --> 02:06.084
♪ HOT CROSS BUNS,
SOMETHING YUMMY ♪

02:06.167 --> 02:07.961
{\an1}♪ TWO WOMEN
OFFERED ME... ♪

02:08.044 --> 02:09.503
PLEASE
STOP SINGING.

02:09.586 --> 02:11.339
IT'S ANNOYING.

02:12.841 --> 02:18.471
{\an1}(<i> softly humming</i>
<i>same tune</i> )

02:18.555 --> 02:20.640
♪ HOT CROSS BUNS... ♪

02:20.723 --> 02:24.727
{\an4}(<i> louder</i> ):
♪ HOT CROSS BUNS,
THEY'RE SO DELICIOUS ♪

02:24.811 --> 02:27.981
{\an4}(<i> echoing</i> ):
♪ I LOVE HOT CROSS BUNS
TO EAT! ♪

02:28.064 --> 02:29.816
Rocko (<i> exasperated</i> ):
HEFFER!

02:31.651 --> 02:33.903
(<i> mumbling</i> )

02:40.952 --> 02:44.914
(<i> explosion</i> )

02:44.998 --> 02:47.333
(<i> tires screeching</i> )

02:49.377 --> 02:50.920
(<i> tires screeching</i> )

02:51.004 --> 02:52.422
BLAZES, WHAT'S
GOING ON?

02:52.505 --> 02:55.925
{\an1}I THINK THE ROAD'S
BLOCKED OR SOMETHING.

02:56.009 --> 02:57.927
SOUNDED LIKE
AN AVALANCHE.

02:58.011 --> 02:59.262
AN AVALANCHE?

02:59.345 --> 03:00.555
WE COULD BE HERE
FOR HOURS.

03:01.222 --> 03:05.143
(<i> horns honking</i> )

03:05.226 --> 03:06.769
{\an3}Heff:
ROCKO!

03:06.853 --> 03:08.605
LOOK-- MT. FROSTY!

03:08.688 --> 03:09.606
LET'S GO!

03:09.689 --> 03:11.274
I TOLD YOU, NO GOOFING OFF.

03:11.357 --> 03:13.693
WE HAVE TO PICK UP
THOSE COMIC BOOKS

03:13.776 --> 03:15.612
AND BE BACK IN O-TOWN
ON TIME.

03:15.695 --> 03:17.947
BESIDES, WE DON'T
HAVE THE MONEY.

03:18.031 --> 03:20.116
BUT ROCKO, IT'S ONLY $5.00.

03:20.199 --> 03:22.368
{\an1}IT'S A SPECIAL,
TODAY ONLY.

03:22.452 --> 03:24.162
$5.00 FOR EVERYTHING.

03:24.245 --> 03:26.623
{\an1}WE HAVE PLENTY OF MONEY
TO COVER THAT.

03:26.706 --> 03:28.625
{\an1}BESIDES, LOOK
AT THIS TRAFFIC.

03:28.708 --> 03:32.253
LIKE YOU SAID, WE'LL
BE STUCK HERE FOR HOURS.

03:32.337 --> 03:34.756
MMM, WELL...

03:34.839 --> 03:38.134
{\an1}OTHER PEOPLE ARE GOING,
THEY'VE GOT THE RIGHT IDEA.

03:38.217 --> 03:40.845
{\an1}I GUESS WE DID GET
A LITTLE EXTRA MONEY.

03:40.929 --> 03:43.097
IT'S FROST-O-RIFIC!

03:43.181 --> 03:45.475
OKAY, LET'S DO SOME SKIING.

03:45.558 --> 03:47.185
ALL RIGHT!

03:47.268 --> 03:47.936
(<i> tires screeching</i> )

03:48.019 --> 03:49.228
(<i> engine backfires</i> )

03:51.230 --> 03:53.399
{\an1}Rocko:
NOW, HEFF, WE CAN'T SPEND

03:53.483 --> 03:56.736
MORE THAN FIVE BUCKS
APIECE, OKAY?

03:56.819 --> 03:57.654
YEAH, SURE, ALL RIGHT.

03:57.737 --> 04:00.990
{\an1}WELCOME TO MT. FROSTY,
IT'S FROST-O-RIFIC.

04:01.074 --> 04:02.700
TWO ALL-DAY PASSES,
PLEASE!

04:02.784 --> 04:04.118
THAT'LL BE $5.00 EACH.

04:04.202 --> 04:05.078
YOU NEED SKIS?

04:05.161 --> 04:07.163
UH, YEAH, HEH, HEH.

04:07.246 --> 04:08.915
UH, I GUESS WE DO.

04:12.460 --> 04:17.298
{\an1}REMEMBER, CHILDREN, ALWAYS KEEP
AN EYE ON YOUR EQUIPMENT.

04:17.382 --> 04:21.344
THERE'S PEOPLE WHO WOULD GRAB
EVERYTHING YOU LEAVE STANDING.

04:21.427 --> 04:23.012
JUST LIKE THAT, GONE.

04:23.096 --> 04:23.304
THEN WHAT DO YOU DO?

04:26.683 --> 04:28.059
HERE YOU GO.

04:28.142 --> 04:30.853
GEE, YOU KNOW, THOSE
LOOK A BIT TOO LONG...

04:30.937 --> 04:32.730
AND I DON'T SKI
THAT WELL...

04:32.814 --> 04:33.856
(<i> loud rustling</i> )

04:37.819 --> 04:39.529
THAT'LL BE $5.00 EACH.

04:39.612 --> 04:41.197
FIVE DOLLARS?

04:41.281 --> 04:42.865
WE ALREADY PAID $5.00!

04:42.949 --> 04:45.660
THE SIGN SAYS,
"EVERYTHING, $5.00."

04:45.743 --> 04:46.869
THAT'S RIGHT.

04:46.953 --> 04:49.372
EVERY <i> THING</i> IS $5.00.

04:49.455 --> 04:51.124
(<i> boing</i> )

04:52.417 --> 04:55.128
(<i> crunching</i> )

04:55.211 --> 04:56.379
(<i> pop</i> )

04:56.462 --> 04:58.381
{\an1}THESE SEEM
A BIT SNUG, HEFF.

04:58.464 --> 05:01.467
{\an5}SNUG, SHMUG--
THEY'RE SUPPOSED
TO BE TIGHT.

05:01.551 --> 05:02.927
COME ON, LET'S GO.

05:04.429 --> 05:07.056
(<i> creaking, Rocko grunting</i> )

05:07.140 --> 05:08.433
(<i> boing</i> )

05:10.810 --> 05:11.394
(<i> boing</i> )

05:13.312 --> 05:14.272
(<i> grunting</i> )

05:14.355 --> 05:15.565
(<i> boing</i> )

05:15.648 --> 05:17.400
(<i> squishy thud</i> )

05:20.278 --> 05:22.113
COME ON, ROCKO!

05:22.196 --> 05:24.240
(<i> Rocko yelling</i> )

05:24.323 --> 05:25.241
(<i> crash</i> )

05:25.324 --> 05:25.408
(<i> goat bleating</i> )

05:27.577 --> 05:29.495
UGH.

05:30.747 --> 05:32.915
FIVE BUCKS
FOR THE CHAIR LIFT...

05:32.999 --> 05:34.959
(<i> sarcastically</i> ):
YOUR GRACE.

05:35.043 --> 05:36.419
FIVE MORE DOLLARS?
THIS IS RIDICULOUS.

05:36.502 --> 05:40.423
{\an4}HEFF, HE'S TRYING
TO MAKE ME...
I REFUSE TO...

05:40.506 --> 05:42.091
{\an1}(<i> grunting</i> ):
HEFFER!

05:42.175 --> 05:43.301
(<i> sighs</i> )

05:43.384 --> 05:45.011
(<i> cash register rings</i> )

05:45.928 --> 05:48.097
{\an1}SEE, ISN'T THIS GREAT,
ROCKO?

05:48.181 --> 05:50.183
FROST-O-RIFIC, HEFF.

05:52.185 --> 05:54.353
(<i> Rocko grunting</i> )

05:55.521 --> 05:57.482
I'LL SEE YOU AT THE TOP,
ROCKO, OKAY?

05:58.858 --> 06:02.320
HEY, PAL, WHY DON'T YOU QUIT
WHILE YOU'RE AHEAD

06:02.403 --> 06:04.280
AND GO HANG OUT IN THE LODGE?

06:04.363 --> 06:06.240
(<i> cash register rings</i> )

06:06.949 --> 06:08.951
(<i> clang</i> )

06:09.035 --> 06:10.036
(<i> Rocko grunts</i> )

06:10.119 --> 06:10.536
(<i> cash register rings</i> )

06:13.539 --> 06:14.499
(<i> clanging, Rocko grunts</i> )

06:20.088 --> 06:20.421
(<i> splat</i> )

06:23.424 --> 06:25.093
(<i> cash register rings</i> )

06:26.928 --> 06:29.430
{\an1}IT'S TIME I GAVE YOU
A FEW POINTERS.

06:30.306 --> 06:32.308
THAT'S GOOD,
YOU'RE DOING FINE.

06:32.391 --> 06:33.684
THERE YOU GO,
THERE YOU GO!

06:33.768 --> 06:34.685
(<i> tires screech</i> )

06:34.769 --> 06:35.978
(<i> crash</i> )

06:37.939 --> 06:40.733
OKAY, HERE WE GO...

06:40.817 --> 06:42.318
KEEP THOSE TIPS UP.

06:42.401 --> 06:44.487
OKAY... OKAY...

06:44.570 --> 06:46.322
HERE COMES THE TREE...

06:46.405 --> 06:48.783
GREAT, YOU PASSED
RIGHT BY IT!

06:48.866 --> 06:49.742
WAY TO GO!

06:49.826 --> 06:50.743
OH...

06:50.827 --> 06:52.745
(<i> thud, Rocko grunts</i> )

06:52.829 --> 06:53.871
OKAY, THIS IS IT

06:53.955 --> 06:56.040
WE'RE NOT GOING
TO HIT ANYTHING.

06:56.124 --> 06:58.334
{\an1}LOOKING GOOD, ROCKO,
ALL RIGHT!

06:58.417 --> 06:59.585
{\an1}WHOO-OO!

06:59.669 --> 07:01.546
AWESOME, GREAT FORM!

07:01.629 --> 07:02.672
{\an1}WATCH IT!

07:02.755 --> 07:04.423
{\an1}(<i> yelling</i> ):
YEAH!

07:09.595 --> 07:11.639
{\an1}GREAT,
YOU DID IT!

07:11.722 --> 07:12.640
I DID IT!

07:12.723 --> 07:14.350
{\an1}HURRAY!

07:14.433 --> 07:15.893
I DID IT! I DID IT...

07:15.977 --> 07:17.770
(<i> clang, thud</i> )

07:20.022 --> 07:22.483
(<i> growling</i> )

07:23.317 --> 07:25.945
TREES, DUMB TREES EVERYWHERE!

07:31.784 --> 07:33.911
(<i> giggles nervously</i> )

07:33.995 --> 07:36.205
TREES... SO GREEN AND GENTLE.

07:36.289 --> 07:38.082
(<i> giggles nervously</i> )

07:38.166 --> 07:42.712
(<i> Rocko screaming</i> )

07:42.795 --> 07:43.629
WAY TO GO, ROCKO!

07:45.214 --> 07:49.177
(<i> loud rumbling</i> )

07:49.260 --> 07:52.054
(<i> tires screeching</i> )

07:52.138 --> 07:54.182
(<i> rumbling</i> )

07:56.184 --> 07:59.353
(<i> crowd chattering</i> )

07:59.437 --> 08:01.898
I <i> LOVE</i> HOT CHOCOLATE
WITH MARSHMALLOWS!

08:01.981 --> 08:03.024
(<i> grunting</i> )

08:03.107 --> 08:04.233
ME, TOO, HEFF.

08:04.317 --> 08:05.359
(<i> fire roaring</i> )

08:05.443 --> 08:06.485
(<i> bell rings</i> )

08:07.445 --> 08:08.237
HEY, ROCKO...

08:08.321 --> 08:08.654
(<i> whistles</i> )

08:10.281 --> 08:11.240
{\an1}(<i> gulps</i> )

08:11.324 --> 08:13.242
(<i> whirring</i> )

08:13.326 --> 08:14.619
(<i> cash register rings</i> )

08:14.702 --> 08:16.913
(<i> fire roaring</i> )

08:17.955 --> 08:19.457
{\an1}Heffer:
I'M TELLING YOU, ROCKO...

08:19.540 --> 08:21.334
YOU ARE READY FOR...

08:21.417 --> 08:24.212
"THE DEVIL'S CREVICE"!

08:25.171 --> 08:27.298
{\an1}NO, HEFF, IT SOUNDS
TOO DANGEROUS.

08:27.381 --> 08:28.591
(<i> cash register rings</i> )

08:28.674 --> 08:32.345
IT'LL BE TEN BUCKS
FOR <i> YOU,</i> BIG GUY.

08:32.428 --> 08:33.511
{\an1}TEN BUCKS?

08:33.596 --> 08:35.056
FORGET THAT!

08:36.265 --> 08:38.934
{\an1}(<i> opening zipper</i> )
I'M TELLING YOU, ROCKO

08:39.018 --> 08:41.354
{\an1}IT'LL BE THE THRILL
OF A LIFETIME!

08:41.437 --> 08:42.270
ABSOLUTELY
NOT!

08:42.355 --> 08:43.438
(<i> zipper closing</i> )

08:43.522 --> 08:44.440
{\an1}IT'S FREE!

08:44.524 --> 08:46.400
FREE?
REALLY?

08:46.484 --> 08:47.818
NOW YOU'RE TALKING.

08:47.902 --> 08:50.112
COME ON, IT'S OVER HERE!

08:50.196 --> 08:52.031
AND THERE'S NO LINE!

08:57.453 --> 09:02.792
(<i> whirring and creaking</i> )

09:02.875 --> 09:04.001
(<i> comet whizzes</i> )

09:05.002 --> 09:06.796
{\an1}HOW'D YOU TALK ME
INTO THIS?

09:06.879 --> 09:07.797
IT'S...

09:07.880 --> 09:08.881
IT'S MADNESS.

09:08.965 --> 09:10.341
I WANT TO GO BACK DOWN.

09:10.424 --> 09:12.051
CAN WE RIDE
BACK DOWN?

09:12.134 --> 09:13.094
SURE.

09:13.427 --> 09:15.805
FOR $5.00.

09:16.597 --> 09:18.474
OH, YES... CERTAINLY.

09:18.557 --> 09:20.559
$5.00... YES, UH, $5.00,
UH, HEH, HEH...

09:20.643 --> 09:23.813
I'VE GOT $5.00...
SOMEWHERE HERE...

09:23.896 --> 09:26.816
I'VE GOT IT...
R-RIGHT HERE... $5.00.

09:26.899 --> 09:28.067
(<i> boing</i> )

09:28.150 --> 09:29.819
(<i> echoing</i> ):
HEFFER?!

09:29.902 --> 09:33.489
WE, WE'VE SPENT ALL
OF MR. SMITTY'S MONEY!

09:33.572 --> 09:35.324
WHAT ARE WE GOING
TO DO?!

09:35.408 --> 09:36.701
I KNOW.

09:36.784 --> 09:38.244
WHAT?

09:38.327 --> 09:39.829
(<i> grinding</i> )

09:39.912 --> 09:42.081
(<i> Rocko screaming</i> )

09:42.164 --> 09:44.500
(<i> wind whistling</i> )

09:44.583 --> 09:47.586
(<i> jet engine roaring</i> )

09:47.670 --> 09:48.713
(<i> bowling pins crashing</i> )

09:51.090 --> 09:53.217
(<i> grunting and screaming</i> )

09:54.218 --> 09:57.221
(<i> crashing and honking</i> )

10:03.352 --> 10:05.354
(<i> jet blasting off</i> )

10:05.438 --> 10:08.524
(<i> Rocko screaming</i> )

10:08.607 --> 10:09.859
(<i> chirping</i> )

10:09.942 --> 10:10.985
(<i> clang</i> )

10:12.111 --> 10:14.572
(<i> ecstatically</i> ):
ISN'T THIS GREAT?!

10:14.655 --> 10:16.574
(<i> sobbing laughter</i> )

10:22.455 --> 10:24.999
(<i> whistling nonchalantly</i> )

10:30.129 --> 10:32.673
WHOO-HOO-HOO!

10:36.427 --> 10:37.636
(<i> shrieks,</i>
<i>antique car horn honks</i> )

10:38.471 --> 10:43.059
(<i> crashing, goat bleating</i> )

10:47.396 --> 10:49.774
(<i> motorcycle engine</i> )

10:52.485 --> 10:53.778
(<i> motorcycle engine</i> )

10:57.156 --> 10:58.616
(<i> clang, Rocko grunts</i> )

11:02.745 --> 11:05.247
"FROST-O SAYS
JUMP AND WIN INSTANTLY."

11:06.665 --> 11:09.293
(<i> bell clanging, shrieking</i> )

11:09.377 --> 11:17.885
(<i> shrieking</i> )

11:20.137 --> 11:24.266
{\an5}Loudspeaker:
Nurse Cardance to the E.R.,
please, Nurse Cardance...

11:24.350 --> 11:26.102
ROCKO!

11:26.185 --> 11:27.478
HOW'RE YOU FEELING?

11:27.561 --> 11:30.439
{\an1}DID THE NURSE GIVE YOU
THE THERMOMETER YET, HUH?

11:30.523 --> 11:32.400
(<i> painfully</i> ):
UH-HUH.

11:32.483 --> 11:35.528
{\an1}I DELIVERED THE COMIC
BOOKS, EVERYTHING'S OKAY.

11:35.611 --> 11:37.154
(<i> thudding</i> )

11:37.238 --> 11:39.115
IT'S A GOOD THING
YOU JUMPED

11:39.198 --> 11:40.950
AND WON ALL
THAT MONEY, HUH?

11:41.033 --> 11:41.992
(<i> grunts</i> )

11:42.076 --> 11:44.286
WE BETTER GO
AND LET YOU REST.

11:44.370 --> 11:46.455
HEY, LET ME TURN ON
THE TV FOR YOU.

11:47.498 --> 11:48.332
{\an1}SEE YA
TAMALE!

11:48.416 --> 11:51.794
(<i> loud thudding, door slamming</i> )

11:51.877 --> 11:53.963
Announcer:
Ski fans!

11:54.046 --> 11:56.298
Thrills, chills, spills!

11:56.382 --> 11:57.675
Ski Mt. Frosty

11:57.758 --> 12:01.470
Everything only $5.00!

12:01.554 --> 12:04.473
{\an1}And don't forget
Mt. Frosty's meanest run--

12:04.557 --> 12:05.516
Devil's Crevice!

12:05.599 --> 12:07.560
It's frost-o-rific!

12:07.643 --> 12:09.979
{\an1}WHAT DO YOU SAY
WE GET ICE CREAM?

12:10.062 --> 12:11.689
CROG NO LIKE ICE CREAM.

12:11.772 --> 12:13.649
{\an1}I KNEW YOU WERE
A BURGER MAN.

12:13.732 --> 12:14.442
(<i> thudding</i> )

12:14.525 --> 12:16.986
OH, SO YOU'RE ROCKO'S PARENTS!

12:17.069 --> 12:19.989
{\an1}WELL, HE'S DOWN THE HALL
AND TO THE RIGHT.

12:33.419 --> 12:35.421
(<i> electrical zapping</i> )

12:35.504 --> 12:38.215
(<i> dog yelping</i> )

12:38.299 --> 12:40.259
(<i> growling and snarling</i> )

12:40.342 --> 12:41.510
(<i> cat snarling</i> )

12:41.594 --> 12:44.722
(<i> barking and growling</i> )

12:44.805 --> 12:46.056
HI, EARL.

12:46.140 --> 12:48.017
I'M YOUR FAIRY DOGMOTHER,
LAVERNE.

12:48.100 --> 12:51.854
{\an1}NOW, I KNOW IN THE PAST
YOU'VE BEEN A BAD DOG

12:51.937 --> 12:54.690
BUT I THINK
YOU'VE LEARNED YOUR LESSON.

12:54.774 --> 12:56.150
IF I LET YOU GO

12:56.233 --> 12:59.570
{\an5}WILL YOU PROMISE
TO BE A GOOD DOGGIE
FROM NOW ON?

12:59.653 --> 13:03.699
(<i> snarling and barking</i> )

13:03.782 --> 13:04.783
MAY I TAKE THAT FOR A YES?

13:13.292 --> 13:16.212
{\an1}GO, EARL, AND BE
A GOOD EXAMPLE TO...

13:16.295 --> 13:17.213
(<i> chomps</i> )

13:17.296 --> 13:20.674
(<i> chews noisily</i> )

13:20.758 --> 13:21.717
(<i> gulps</i> )

13:21.800 --> 13:23.302
(<i> squeaking</i> )

13:23.385 --> 13:32.019
(<i> prison siren wailing</i> )

13:34.396 --> 13:35.439
(<i> tires screeching</i> )

13:35.523 --> 13:36.941
(<i> humming</i> )

13:37.024 --> 13:40.903
(<i> heavy breathing</i>
<i>in bushes</i> )

13:40.986 --> 13:44.782
{\an1}Mrs. Bighead:
HONEY, IT'S THE FLY MAN!

13:45.533 --> 13:47.409
OH, GOOD MORNING, DAN.

13:47.493 --> 13:49.119
GOOD MORNING, MRS. BIGHEAD.

13:49.203 --> 13:51.622
GOT SOME REAL FRESH ONES
FOR YOU TODAY.

13:51.705 --> 13:54.250
OOH, THEY ALL LOOK SO GOOD.

13:54.333 --> 13:56.252
THAT ONE IN THE CORNER...

13:56.335 --> 13:57.878
{\an1}HE'S DISEASED,
ISN'T HE?

13:57.962 --> 14:00.089
OH, YES,
MA'AM!

14:00.172 --> 14:01.799
OOH, THEY LOOK DELISH!

14:01.882 --> 14:04.802
{\an4}OH, BETTER CUT
NEXT WEEK'S ORDER
IN HALF.

14:04.885 --> 14:07.304
{\an1}MR. BIGHEAD
IS ON A LITTLE DIET.

14:07.388 --> 14:08.847
OH, YES.

14:08.931 --> 14:10.766
SEE YOU TOMORROW!

14:10.849 --> 14:11.642
TOODLE-OO.

14:11.725 --> 14:16.772
(<i> growling</i> )

14:16.855 --> 14:24.321
(<i> growling continues</i> )

14:27.157 --> 14:29.285
WHEW.

14:29.368 --> 14:31.036
(<i> snarling</i> )

14:31.120 --> 14:32.955
(<i> panting</i> )

14:33.038 --> 14:34.290
HA... HEH HEH...

14:34.373 --> 14:37.626
SPUNKY, YOU HAD ME
SHAKING IN MY BOOTS.

14:37.710 --> 14:39.795
(<i> chomping, screaming</i> )

14:39.878 --> 14:41.630
(<i> growling</i> )

14:41.714 --> 14:42.881
(<i> chomping</i> )

14:42.965 --> 14:46.343
NOW, ED, THESE
AREN'T FOR YOU.

14:46.427 --> 14:48.846
YOU'RE ON A DIET.

14:48.929 --> 14:49.638
REMEMBER?

14:49.722 --> 14:52.850
HERE'S <i> YOUR</i>
BREAKFAST.

14:52.933 --> 14:54.560
WHAT IS THIS?

14:54.643 --> 14:55.936
IT'S COTTAGE CHEESE.

14:58.188 --> 15:00.232
ONE CURD?

15:00.316 --> 15:01.609
IF IT'S TOO MUCH

15:01.692 --> 15:03.360
{\an1}I CAN CUT IT
IN HALF FOR YOU.

15:05.487 --> 15:07.698
GOOD, YOU'RE DONE.

15:07.781 --> 15:09.908
{\an1}HURRY UP, OR YOU'LL BE LATE
FOR WORK, DARLING.

15:09.992 --> 15:13.495
{\an1}OOH, OOH...
AND DROP THIS IN THE TRASH

15:13.579 --> 15:14.830
ON YOUR WAY TO THE CAR.

15:16.540 --> 15:21.378
(<i> snarling</i> )

15:22.421 --> 15:24.256
(<i> snarls</i> )

15:25.215 --> 15:26.216
(<i> bullet ricocheting</i> )

15:26.300 --> 15:27.926
(<i> yelling</i> )

15:28.010 --> 15:31.013
(<i> chomping, yelling</i> )

15:31.096 --> 15:33.766
(<i> yelling</i> )

15:33.849 --> 15:35.184
(<i> shrieking</i> )

15:35.267 --> 15:39.355
(<i> yelling, barking</i> )

15:39.438 --> 15:43.233
(<i> barking, thudding</i> )

15:43.317 --> 15:44.360
(<i> barking</i> )

15:44.443 --> 15:45.361
UH-OH.

15:45.444 --> 15:47.363
(<i> chomping</i> )

15:47.446 --> 15:49.865
(<i> rumbling, yelling</i> )

15:49.948 --> 15:50.741
(<i> yelling</i> )

15:50.824 --> 15:51.950
(<i> thudding</i> )

15:52.868 --> 15:54.495
(<i> roaring</i> )

15:55.079 --> 15:56.080
(<i> barking</i> )

15:56.163 --> 15:57.706
(<i> tires screeching, crashing</i> )

15:58.582 --> 16:00.417
(<i> tires screeching, barking</i> )

16:00.501 --> 16:03.420
(<i> growling, tires screeching</i> )

16:04.838 --> 16:06.340
(<i> growls</i> )

16:10.678 --> 16:11.011
(<i> clang</i> )

16:13.639 --> 16:15.432
ALL RIGHT,
FLEA BAG!

16:16.767 --> 16:17.726
DROP THE FLORA

16:17.810 --> 16:20.062
OR YOU'LL REGRET
THE DAY YOU WERE WEANED.

16:20.145 --> 16:24.900
(<i> "The Good, Bad,</i>
<i>and the Ugly" playing</i> )

16:24.983 --> 16:27.027
(<i> joints crunching</i> )

16:28.987 --> 16:29.947
(<i> clang</i> )

16:30.030 --> 16:31.031
(<i> growls</i> )

16:31.615 --> 16:33.659
{\an1}(<i> growls</i> )

16:33.742 --> 16:35.452
PUT THOSE FLOWERS BACK!

16:35.536 --> 16:37.579
(<i> whimpering</i> )

16:37.663 --> 16:39.832
(<i> whimpering</i> )

16:37.663 --> 16:39.832
(<i> grunting</i> )

16:39.915 --> 16:41.917
THAT'S RIGHT,
THAT'S RIGHT...

16:42.000 --> 16:43.919
PUT 'EM BACK!

16:46.171 --> 16:47.715
(<i> whimpering</i> )

16:51.009 --> 16:53.262
OH, IT'S OKAY.

16:53.345 --> 16:54.930
I DIDN'T MEAN
TO FRIGHTEN YOU.

16:55.013 --> 16:56.306
(<i> whimpers</i> )

16:56.390 --> 16:58.142
HERE, SMELL MY HAND.

16:59.685 --> 17:02.521
(<i> yells</i> ):
SMELL IT!

17:02.604 --> 17:03.647
(<i> sniffs</i> )

17:03.731 --> 17:05.357
THAT'S RIGHT.

17:05.441 --> 17:06.442
(<i> pop</i> )

17:06.525 --> 17:08.819
SEE, I WON'T
HURT YOU.

17:08.902 --> 17:11.113
(<i> whistling, heart pounding</i> )

17:11.195 --> 17:12.948
(<i> gulps</i> )

17:13.031 --> 17:15.909
OH, YOU POOR BABY.

17:15.992 --> 17:17.618
WHAT'S THIS?

17:17.703 --> 17:20.122
EARL DOG SPECIMEN...

17:20.204 --> 17:21.123
(<i> gasps</i> )

17:21.205 --> 17:25.210
OH, SOLD
FOR SCIENCE EXPERIMENTS!

17:25.294 --> 17:27.963
{\an1}OH, I KNOW THE TORMENT
YOU HAVE ENDURED.

17:28.047 --> 17:33.177
OH, YOU POOR, PATHETIC,
MISUNDERSTOOD WRETCH!

17:33.260 --> 17:36.388
LET ME CLUTCH YOU
TO MY BOSOM.

17:36.472 --> 17:39.516
AS GOD IS MY WITNESS

17:39.600 --> 17:44.855
{\an1}YOU WILL NEVER BE PRODDED
IN THE NAME OF SCIENCE AGAIN!

17:47.900 --> 17:49.318
(<i> tires screech</i> )

17:57.785 --> 17:59.369
(<i> sighs</i> )

17:59.703 --> 18:03.040
{\an1}OH, ED...

18:03.123 --> 18:05.334
I ADOPTED A PUPPY.

18:05.417 --> 18:07.419
(<i> yelling</i> ):
NO!

18:08.170 --> 18:09.546
BEV, GET AWAY FROM HIM!

18:09.630 --> 18:10.839
HE'S A BONE-CRUSHING

18:10.923 --> 18:13.675
{\an5}BUICK-DISMANTLING,
POORLY DRAWN,
BACKBITING

18:13.759 --> 18:15.677
KILLING MACHINE!

18:17.096 --> 18:18.388
UH-HUH.

18:18.472 --> 18:20.224
LET ME EXPLAIN THIS TO YOU.

18:20.307 --> 18:21.767
THIS IS EARL.

18:21.850 --> 18:25.020
{\an1}HE IS OUR DOG NOW,
AND I LOVE HIM LIKE A SON

18:25.103 --> 18:25.979
AND YOU WILL, TOO

18:26.063 --> 18:28.398
OR YOU WILL GET
EVEN LESS TO EAT

18:28.482 --> 18:29.233
THAN YOU GET NOW.

18:32.277 --> 18:36.073
{\an5}Mrs. Bighead:
ED, IF YOU BURN A FEW CALORIES
PLAYING WITH EARL

18:36.156 --> 18:39.034
MAYBE WE COULD CHEAT A LITTLE
ON YOUR DIET.

18:39.117 --> 18:40.118
HAVE FUN, BOYS!

18:40.202 --> 18:41.286
(<i> growls</i> )

18:41.370 --> 18:42.371
(<i> gulps</i> )

18:42.454 --> 18:44.706
(<i> growls</i> )

18:45.290 --> 18:48.460
(<i> barking</i> )

18:48.544 --> 18:50.087
(<i> yelling</i> )

18:50.170 --> 18:52.464
(<i> chomping, snarling</i> )

18:52.548 --> 18:53.465
(<i> yelling</i> )

18:53.549 --> 18:54.800
(<i> crash</i> )

18:54.883 --> 18:56.969
WHOA, HE'S BITING MY BUTT, OUCH!

18:57.052 --> 18:59.054
(<i> chomping, crashing</i> )

18:59.137 --> 19:00.764
(<i> yelling</i> ):
BEV!

19:00.848 --> 19:01.765
(<i> chomping</i> )

19:01.849 --> 19:03.767
(<i> yelling</i> )

19:03.851 --> 19:04.768
(<i> crash</i> )

19:04.852 --> 19:05.894
(<i> barking, yelling</i> )

19:05.978 --> 19:08.480
I WONDER IF I HAVE ANY NUTMEG.

19:09.439 --> 19:12.067
HERE'S YOUR DINNER,
EARLSIE.

19:12.150 --> 19:13.694
<i>BON APPETIT.</i>

19:15.612 --> 19:16.989
{\an1}HERE, ED.

19:17.072 --> 19:18.949
{\an1}SINCE YOU'VE BEEN
PLAYING SO HARD

19:19.032 --> 19:21.076
{\an1}I GAVE YOU
A DOUBLE PORTION.

19:21.159 --> 19:23.412
(<i> snarling</i> )

19:23.495 --> 19:25.414
(<i> splattering</i> )

19:25.497 --> 19:28.083
(<i> chomping, grunting</i> )

19:28.166 --> 19:29.334
(<i> bullet ricocheting</i> )

19:39.344 --> 19:41.847
(<i> banging</i> )

19:41.930 --> 19:44.182
(<i> boing</i> )

19:44.266 --> 19:45.350
(<i> high-pitched babble</i> )

19:45.434 --> 19:48.103
OH, MOM, YOU SHOULD
SEE THEM TOGETHER.

19:48.186 --> 19:50.105
ED IS OUT GIVING EARL A BATH.

19:50.188 --> 19:51.106
(<i> yelling</i> )

19:51.189 --> 19:53.400
(<i> gurgling</i> )

19:55.360 --> 19:57.029
ARE YOU CLEAN NOW?

19:57.112 --> 20:00.073
OH, WELL, HERE'S
A NICE TREAT FOR YOU.

20:00.657 --> 20:02.951
(<i> sobbing</i> )

20:03.035 --> 20:06.622
{\an5}ED, WHY DON'T YOU
TAKE THE DOG OUT
FOR A WALK?

20:06.705 --> 20:08.874
{\an1}I AM NOT TAKING
THE DOG OUT AGAIN!

20:08.957 --> 20:11.460
OH, ED, YOU JUST
HAVEN'T BONDED YET.

20:11.543 --> 20:15.130
IF HE'S A GOOD BOY,
YOU CAN GIVE HIM THIS STEAK.

20:15.213 --> 20:16.715
{\an1}OH... YES.

20:16.798 --> 20:19.134
WELL, MAYBE WE SHOULD BOND.

20:19.217 --> 20:21.053
COME ON, EARLSIE.

20:21.136 --> 20:25.015
LET'S SPEND SOME
QUALITY TIME TOGETHER, HUH?

20:25.098 --> 20:26.224
JUST YOU, ME...

20:27.768 --> 20:30.062
AND... THE STEAK.

20:30.145 --> 20:31.939
(<i> chuckling wickedly</i> )

20:33.065 --> 20:37.194
{\an1}YOU DON'T THINK I COULD
JUST HAVE A, A LITTLE BITE...

20:37.277 --> 20:37.402
{\an1}NO!

20:40.238 --> 20:41.490
THAT'S IT!

20:41.573 --> 20:43.784
IT'S HIM OR ME!

20:45.243 --> 20:47.829
(<i> coyly</i> ):
OH, EARLSIE.

20:47.913 --> 20:49.831
(<i> cat yowling</i> )

20:49.915 --> 20:52.000
LOOK WHAT I
HAVE FOR YOU.

20:52.084 --> 20:53.919
(<i> snarls, gulps</i> )

20:54.002 --> 20:57.047
HELPLESS VICTIMS.

20:57.130 --> 21:00.175
(<i> snarling</i> )

21:00.259 --> 21:02.052
(<i> heavy door slams shut</i> )

21:02.135 --> 21:03.178
(<i> engine starts</i> )

21:04.429 --> 21:05.681
(<i> tires screeching</i> )

21:05.764 --> 21:09.434
(<i> laughing, Earl barking</i> )

21:09.518 --> 21:11.645
(<i> tires screeching</i> )

21:11.728 --> 21:13.021
OH, EARL...

21:13.105 --> 21:16.274
{\an1}I'VE GOT A NICE,
JUICY FLY MAN FOR YOU.

21:16.358 --> 21:18.235
(<i> laughing</i> )

21:18.318 --> 21:25.534
(<i> Ed laughing, Earl snarling</i> )

21:25.617 --> 21:27.035
(<i> continues laughing</i> )

21:27.119 --> 21:29.371
(<i> laughter echoes</i> )

21:29.454 --> 21:31.623
(<i> continues laughing</i> )

21:31.707 --> 21:33.917
(<i> laughing, tires screeching</i> )

21:34.001 --> 21:35.836
(<i> rocket engines firing</i> )

21:37.546 --> 21:43.051
(<i> snarling</i> )

21:43.135 --> 21:44.136
(<i> chomps</i> )

21:45.679 --> 21:46.805
(<i> tires screech</i> )

21:48.473 --> 21:49.808
(<i> tires screech</i> )

21:52.644 --> 21:55.897
(<i> satellite beeping</i> )

21:56.773 --> 21:57.899
(<i> tires screech</i> )

21:59.985 --> 22:03.030
ED, HONEY, HAVE
YOU SEEN EARL?

22:05.198 --> 22:06.700
UH... OH, YES, YES.

22:06.783 --> 22:08.285
HE'S OUT BACK.

22:11.038 --> 22:13.623
HOW'S MY BABY EARL?

22:13.707 --> 22:17.127
{\an4}OH, MY, WE'RE
ENERGETIC TODAY,
AREN'T WE?

22:17.210 --> 22:19.504
OH, YOU'RE SO CUTE.

22:19.588 --> 22:21.214
ALL RIGHT, EARL...

22:21.298 --> 22:22.966
HERE'S YOUR NICE...

22:23.050 --> 22:28.597
(<i> whirring</i> )

22:28.680 --> 22:30.432
EXCUSE ME, MA'AM...

22:31.516 --> 22:33.852
IS THIS YOURS?

22:33.935 --> 22:35.437
EARL!

22:37.522 --> 22:39.733
{\an1}WANT TO KEEP IT
ON A LEASH?

22:42.527 --> 22:50.786
(<i> grunting, panting happily</i> )

22:50.869 --> 22:52.204
THAT'S IT, THAT'S IT!

22:52.287 --> 22:54.122
I HAVE BEEN MASHED, PUMMELLED

22:54.206 --> 22:56.666
BITTEN, SCRATCHED,
FETCHED, BURIED

22:56.750 --> 22:59.878
{\an1}AND REDUCED TO WEARING
THIS RIDICULOUS COSTUME.

22:59.961 --> 23:02.130
I'M CALLING THE POUND!

23:02.214 --> 23:04.049
ED, YOU'RE NOT SERIOUS!

23:04.132 --> 23:06.134
YOU BET YOUR BUTT
I'M SERIOUS!

23:06.218 --> 23:08.136
BUT, ED, BUT,
ED, BUT, ED...

23:08.220 --> 23:09.096
HELLO, DOG POUND?

23:09.179 --> 23:11.640
{\an1}I'D LIKE TO REPORT
A VICIOUS DOG.

23:11.723 --> 23:12.516
WHAT?! YES, I'LL HOLD.

23:15.727 --> 23:17.646
MA'AM.

23:23.902 --> 23:25.278
(<i> barking</i> )

23:25.362 --> 23:28.156
FEEDING TIME, YOO-HOO!

23:28.240 --> 23:34.496
(<i> barking, fighting</i> )

23:34.579 --> 23:36.665
OH, MY GOSH,
IT'S REAL FOOD!

23:36.748 --> 23:39.084
OH-HO... SHOO, SHOO,
SHOO, GO AWAY!

23:39.167 --> 23:40.877
{\an1}DON'T EVEN THINK
ABOUT IT!

23:40.961 --> 23:42.838
(<i> growling, chomping</i> )

23:42.921 --> 23:44.673
(<i> groans</i> )

23:44.756 --> 23:47.884
I HATE MY LIFE.

23:54.182 --> 23:59.354
